n with staff and their representatives.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In the UK we have a collective bargaining agreement with the PCS union. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">As of the end of August, the percentage of UK appointed staff that were members of a union was 45.8%. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Staff representation overseas will vary and reflect local practice and legislation. The management of a staff association will vary depending on the size of the office. In a small office, it might be a simple and informal process where staff elect one or two staff representatives on an annual basis. In a larger office, a more formal approach might be taken. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Details on local membership levels and management arrangements are not held centrally.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In the UK and overseas we review staff pay annually and a review is subject to consultations with trade unions and staff associations. Typically the areas we would consult on are the outcomes of salary benchmarking against the market, changes to pay policy and uplifts to pay bands. In the UK the PCS union provides the British Council with a pay claim which forms the basis of initial consultations. In the UK and overseas pay claims and final pay offers are shared with staff as part of the consultation process.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">We seek to be an attractive and fair employer and to demon</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">strate good employer practice. For example, a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">l our staff in the UK are paid </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the living wage. We also offe</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">r paid internships which enable</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> people from a diversity of backgrounds to take up these opportunities. We are also particularly proud of our family friendly policies</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> which include</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> flexible working, attractive maternity and paternity benefits and support t</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">owards the cost of childcare.</span></p><p style="font-size:11pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">19 November 2013</span></p></div></body></html>